config FLASH_RPI_PICO_FIXED
	bool "OpenJBOD RP2040 flash driver (sub-page write fix)"
	default n
	depends on DT_HAS_RASPBERRYPI_PICO_FLASH_CONTROLLER_ENABLED
	depends on !FLASH_RPI_PICO
	select FLASH_HAS_DRIVER_ENABLED
	select FLASH_HAS_PAGE_LAYOUT
	select FLASH_HAS_EXPLICIT_ERASE
	select PICOSDK_USE_FLASH
	help
	  Drop-in replacement for the in-tree FLASH_RPI_PICO driver. The Pico SDK's
	  flash_write_partial() (sub-page program via direct SSI bit-bang) silently
	  fails on the OpenJBOD W25Q128, so MCUboot image-trailer and settings/NVS
	  sub-page writes never reach the chip ("could not set the boot bit"). This
	  driver performs sub-page writes as a read-modify-write of the containing
	  256-byte page via the working bootrom flash_range_program().

	  To use: set CONFIG_FLASH_RPI_PICO=n and CONFIG_FLASH_RPI_PICO_FIXED=y.
	  Must be enabled for every image that writes flash - the application and,
	  when MCUboot is built via sysbuild, the mcuboot image (sysbuild/mcuboot.conf).
